<subSubSection id="C3296509FFAAFF91FF4DF9E9FEB07238" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8C3682FFAAFF97FF4DF9E9FEC97545" blockId="3.[144,1126,1580,1676]" box="[144,295,1580,1606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAAFF97FF4DF9E9FEC97545" bold="true" box="[144,295,1580,1606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C3682FFAAFF90FF4DF98AFC72778E" blockId="3.[144,1126,1580,1676]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1134,1002,1165]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName id="4C334D01FFAAFF97FF4DF98AFE8F756A" authorityName=", Eversmann" authorityYear="1852" box="[144,353,1615,1641]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="florivaga">
<emphasis id="B947EA90FFAAFF97FF4DF98AFE8F756A" box="[144,353,1615,1641]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Andrena florivaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a une large distribution paléarctique. En effet, des observations ont été signalées de 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFAAFF97FE9BF9B4FE7D7588" box="[326,403,1649,1675]" name="France" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">France</collectingCountry>
jusqu’au centre de la Sibérie (région du lac Baikal) et de 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFAAFF97FBD3F9B4FB887588" box="[1038,1126,1649,1675]" name="Turkey" pageId="3" pageNumber="72">Turquie</collectingCountry>
jusqu’en 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFADFF90FF22FC2FFEB27707" box="[255,348,1002,1028]" name="Poland" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Pologne</collectingCountry>
(voir 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFADFF90FE7CFC2FFD607706" author="Banaszak J. &amp; Motyka E. &amp; Szczepko K." box="[417,654,1002,1029]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="45 - 50" refId="ref4533" refString="Banaszak J., Motyka E. &amp; Szczepko K. 2013. Andrena florivaga Eversmann, 1852 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Andrenidae) - A New Bee Species of the Genus Andrena in Poland. Journal of Apicultural Science 57: 45 - 50." type="journal article" year="2013">Banaszak et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
et publications citées). La distribution de l’espèce semble s’être élargie récemment, la 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFADFF90FD46FBC9FD0B7725" box="[667,741,1036,1062]" name="Switzerland" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Suisse</collectingCountry>
étant le second pays, après la Po- logne (en 2004, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFADFF90FE92FBEBFDD3774A" author="Banaszak J. &amp; Motyka E. &amp; Szczepko K." box="[335,573,1070,1097]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="45 - 50" refId="ref4533" refString="Banaszak J., Motyka E. &amp; Szczepko K. 2013. Andrena florivaga Eversmann, 1852 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Andrenidae) - A New Bee Species of the Genus Andrena in Poland. Journal of Apicultural Science 57: 45 - 50." type="journal article" year="2013">Banaszak et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
), où l’espèce a été observée pour la première fois après les années 2000. Plus globalement, l’espèce semble être en expansion dans le Nord de l’Europe, notamment en 
<collectingCountry id="F3247612FFADFF90FDC5FBB7FD79778F" box="[536,663,1138,1164]" name="Germany" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Allemagne</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA24B73FFADFF90FD7BFBB7FC7E778E" author="Westrich P. &amp; Frommer U. &amp; Mandery K. &amp; Riemann H. &amp; Ruhnke H. &amp; Saure C. &amp; Voith J." box="[678,912,1138,1165]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" pagination="373 - 416" refId="ref5034" refString="Westrich P., Frommer U., Mandery K., Riemann H., Ruhnke H., Saure C. &amp; Voith J. 2012. Rote Liste und Gesamtartenliste der Bienen (Hymenoptera, Apidae) Deutschlands. 5. Fassung, Stand Februar 2011. Naturschutz und Biologische Vielfalt 3: 373 - 416." type="journal article" year="2012">Westrich et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
